    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix segmentation fault in M2AP MCE setup response generation\n\n### Summary\nThe `m2ap_MCE_generate_m2_setup_response` function in `m2ap_MCE_generate_messages.c` was not properly populating the required Information Elements, causing segmentation faults when the incomplete message was encoded and sent over the network. This occurred because all the actual data population code was commented out, leaving only empty IE structures.\n\nThis fix implements the complete M2 Setup Response message generation with proper IE population.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_MCE_generate_messages.c`: Completely reimplemented the `m2ap_MCE_generate_m2_setup_response` function to properly populate all required IEs including GlobalMCE_ID, optional MCEname, and MCCHrelatedBCCH_ConfigPerMBSFNArea.\n- `openair3/UTILS/conversions.h`: Added `MACRO_MCE_ID_TO_BIT_STRING` macro for proper MCE ID to BIT STRING conversion.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the original issue:\n1. Configure an MCE with M2 interface\n2. Trigger an M2 Setup procedure\n3. The MCE would attempt to generate an M2 Setup Response using the broken function\n4. Segmentation fault would occur during ASN.1 encoding due to improperly populated IEs\n\nWith this fix, the M2 Setup Response is properly generated and the M2 interface establishment succeeds.\n"
}